class anaplan_api.ActionParser.ActionParser(results: dict, url: str)[source]¶

Bases: anaplan_api.Parser.Parser

Represents a parser for Anaplan actions. This class parses and stores the results of an Anaplan task.

Parameters

results (List[ParserResponse]) – ParserResponse object with the details of an executed Anaplan task

__init__(results: dict, url: str)[source]¶

This Parser class does not require a AnaplanConnection object because this action type does not generate an error dump, nor output a file that would require further API calls.

Parameters

  • results (dict) – JSON response object with the details of an executed action

anaplan_api.KeystoreManager module¶

class anaplan_api.KeystoreManager.KeystoreManager(path, passphrase, alias, key_pass)[source]¶

Bases: object

Create a KeystoreManager object, which extracts and stores the public certificate and private key from a Java Keystore. It is initialized with the path to the Java Keystore, passphrase to open the keystore, alias of the desired key-pair, and the passphrase for the private key. At initialization, the certificate and private key are extracted and stored in the object.

Parameters

  • path (str) – Path to the Java Keystore

  • passphrase (str) – Passphrase to open the keystore

  • alias (str) – Alias of the desired key-pair in the store

  • key_pass (str) – Passphrase to read the private key

  • key (bytes) – Byte array of the specified key in base64 format

  • cert (str) – String containing the certificate text in base64 format

__init__(path, passphrase, alias, key_pass)[source]¶
Parameters

  • path – Path to the Java Keystore

  • passphrase – Passphrase to open the keystore

  • alias – Alis of the desired key-pair in the store

  • key_pass – Passphrase to read the private key.

get_keystore_pair()[source]¶

Opens the keystore to read the specified key-pair. The strings are padded with the expected header and footer for RSA keys.

Raises

  • BadKeystoreFormatException – Structural error occurred while parsing the keystore

  • UnsupportedKeystoreVersionException – Unspecified or unsupported keystore version

  • KeystoreSignatureException – Specified password for keystore is invalid

  • DuplicateAliasException – Error if keystore contains duplicates of the specified alias

  • DecryptionFailureException – Error decrypting keystore entry

  • UnexpectedAlgorithmException – Unexpected cryptographic algorithm used in keystore
